  pm-nilh,related,"2026-07-06T08:03:45.495Z",null,null
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/435\n\n## Problem\n`--json` output serializes every field including nulls and empty containers: `pm list --json` always emits a 23-key all-null `filters` echo (+ empty `runtime_filters`); `pm context --json` echoes `order/deadline/assignee/parent: null` per item. Measured: list 2552 B (TOON) vs 3773 B JSON (+48%); context 4582 vs 7034 (+53%). AGENTS.md already warns agents off `--json` for loops — the structured format is too expensive for the agents that need it.\n\n## Proposed fix\nLean JSON mode (`--json --lean`, `PM_JSON_LEAN=1`, or config key) that omits null values, empty arrays/objects, and collapses `filters` to only keys actually set (TOON parity). Verbose form stays as explicit opt-in.\n\n## Definition of done\nLean mode on list/get/context/search JSON paths; measured >=40% size cut on list+context in a tag-heavy tracker; contracts + docs updated; spec pins the null-omission rules."
